1) Resources Folder
AuthUserBean.json  
Contains:

userName

password

token

userId

requestPayload.json  
Example content:

json
{
  "name": "Apple MacBook Pro 16",
  "data": {
    "year": 2019,
    "price": 1849.99,
    "CPU model": "Intel Core i9",
    "Hard disk size": "1 TB"
  }
}
2) Package: com.maveric.objectapi.auth
AuthUserBean.java

Fields: userName, password, token, userId

Default constructor

Parameterized constructor

Getter and setter methods

toString() method

3) Package: com.maveric.objectapi.pojos
Object.java

Fields: id, name, data, color, capacity, year, price, createdAt, updatedAt

Default constructor

Parameterized constructor

Getter and setter methods

ObjectTobeAdd.java

Fields: id, name

Default constructor

Parameterized constructor

Getter and setter methods

4) Package: com.maveric.objectapi.test
Contains test methods to perform all positive and negative scenarios defined in the API Automation Capstone Project.

Requirements:

Use @BeforeAll, @AfterAll, and @Order annotations for setup, teardown, and test ordering.

Implement tests using Rest Assured matcher patterns.

Utilize List and HashMap where applicable for handling response data.
